The paper deals with designing optimal in-place algorithms for basic graph problems, which suggests that it belongs to the data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.DM) categories. The paper also involves the study of connectivity and decomposition problems, which are closely related to computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper involves the use of sortedness in the input representation, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG).
